Cap back in action! In this episode of the Major Issues Podcast, the crew dives into Captain America: Brave New World, breaking down everything we know so far about Sam Wilson’s first solo outing as Cap. From behind-the-scenes shake-ups to rumored plot details and character returns, we discuss what this movie means for the MCU and where it could take the franchise next. Will Sam’s Captain America rise to the challenge? What role does the Leader play? And how does this film set the stage for what’s to come? Suit up and join the conversation! 

Please leave us a review on [ITunes](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us wherever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by ComicBook Clique, the only stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.

